rComments: I agree that he is a fantastic lecturer and you will need to attend to do well. Really. Smart. But he is really a sweetheart and funny.  This was different from my other religion courses in a good way - lots of thinking about the sciences, the humanities, role of the university, and basically everything.  Very intellectual but you won't regret it!

Surprised not to see more reviews up.  I took his atheism course last summer....  Tons of ideas that connected with my other classes this year and with my life in general.  He got me to tune in to things.
Very clear but also pretty dense lectures, and friendly outside of class.  Young but smart as hell, also funny as hell!  Pretty inspiring actually.
